# Installation

Download and install Anaconda: https://www.anaconda.com/  

## Setting up our environment
###Anaconda:  

1. Create test environment
```bash
conda create -n testenv python=3.6 
```

2. Activate our new test environment
```bash
conda activate testenv 
```

3. Install our dependencies
```bash
pip install -r application/requirements.txt
```

# Running our application

To run our code from the commandline we need to make sure that our test environment we created in step 1 is active.
```bash
conda activate testenv
```

We can run our code from commandline like:
```bash
python3 application/main.py
```

Our application will be running on http://localhost:8080
